The paper discusses side-channel attacks and their impact on security and privacy of devices, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The use of machine learning for application inference is a key aspect of the paper, which suggests that it could also be relevant to sub-categories such as software engineering (cs.SE) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the use of features extracted from EM side-channel emissions and software exposed DVFS states, which could be relevant to sub-categories such as computer architecture (cs.AR) and systems and control (cs.SY).
